    "body": "> that means that whether the user has rejoined the community or not is simply a product of them being online or offline after the new control node has come online, is that correct? And if permissions have changed, they would be kicked and not appear in the members list anyway.\r\n\r\nYeah pretty much. Unless the permissions changed, the user can auto rejoin by just going back online.\r\n\r\n> If we do want to amend the UI to flag which of the members are yet to re-share their addresses and rejoin we could do something minimal like the below but I think this is only needed if we can identify the core use case for the owner differentiating between the \"ghost\" members and those that have rejoined. Off the top of my head, I suppose it would be useful to know how many of my community I will actually reach with @everyone type messages etc?\r\n\r\nI guess so yes. We wanted something because the people are not actually members until they come back online, so even though the owner could see the members in the management UI, in the chat UI, you won't see anyone.\r\n\r\nKnowing who didn't join back can also be helpful in case something went wrong (lost message). That way, the owner can tell the user to leave the community and send a new request to join.",
