    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "> How can we solve it - send old requests to join from an old owner to the new one and update only state (waiting for an auto-rejoin)\r\n\r\nIMO, asking the old owner for the request to join, even though most of the time it would return the right data, cannot be trusted, since the old owner could just go away forever at that point as well.\r\n\r\nSo asking the old owner just for the date joined seems like a strain on the network and more complexity on our side for a very small gain. I think it would simpler to just show an \"unknown date\" or  a symbol until we do get the data from the users back.",
